Electrical (Added, Ord. No. 2011-06)
440.01. State electrical code. 
	Subdivision 1. Authority. The purpose of this ordinance is to establish an electrical inspections program administered and enforced by the City. The Minnesota Electrical Act, as adopted by the Commissioner of Labor and Industry pursuant to Minnesota Statutes Sections 326B.31 to 326B.399, as amended, is hereby incorporated into this ordinance as if fully set out herein. The Minnesota State Building Code incorporates by reference the National Electrical Code pursuant to Minn. R. 1315.0020, as amended. All such codes incorporated herein by reference constitute the electrical code of the City of Crystal.
	Subd. 2. Authority to inspect. The City hereby provides for the inspection of all electrical installations, pursuant to Minn. Stat. ยง 326B.36. subd. 6, as amended.
	Subd. 3. Compliance. All electrical installations shall comply with the requirements of the electrical code of the City and this ordinance.
	Subd. 4. Permits and fees. The issuance of permits and the collection of fees shall be as authorized in Minnesota Statutes 326B.37, as amended, and in Appendix IV of this code.
	Subd. 5. Notice and appeal. All notices of violations and orders issued under this ordinance shall be in conformance with Minn. Stat. ยง 326B.36, subd. 4, as amended.
	Subd. 6. Sunset. This ordinance may be revoked by the city council once the Department of Labor and Industry is funded for the 2011 fiscal year by legislative enactment of a state budget. 
